Minimal testnet support patch for Passivbot Hyperliquid connector.

Target: bots/passivbot/src/exchanges/hyperliquid.py, create_ccxt_sessions()

Passivbot has no testnet support — `create_ccxt_sessions()` always instantiates
CCXT HL clients with default (mainnet) URLs and mainnet EIP-712 signing. CCXT
itself supports HL sandbox mode via `set_sandbox_mode(True)`, which swaps URLs
to `api.hyperliquid-testnet.xyz` AND flips the phantom-agent `source` field
from "a" to "b" so testnet rejects mainnet-format signatures correctly.

Reading `use_testnet` from the per-user `api-keys.json` entry keeps the patch
minimal and scoped: only users that explicitly opt in get testnet routing.

--- a/src/exchanges/hyperliquid.py
+++ b/src/exchanges/hyperliquid.py
@@ -56,6 +56,7 @@ class HyperliquidBot(...):
     def create_ccxt_sessions(self):
         creds = {
             "walletAddress": self.user_info["wallet_address"],
             "privateKey": self.user_info["private_key"],
         }
+        use_testnet = bool(self.user_info.get("use_testnet", False))
         # Configure fetchMarkets to include HIP-3 stock perps from TradeXYZ
         fetch_markets_config = {
             "types": ["swap", "hip3"],  # Include HIP-3 markets
             "hip3": {
                 "dex": ["xyz"],  # TradeXYZ DEX for stock perps (TSLA, NVDA, etc.)
             },
         }
         if self.ws_enabled:
             self.ccp = getattr(ccxt_pro, self.exchange)(creds)
             self.ccp.options.update(self._build_ccxt_options())
             self.ccp.options["defaultType"] = "swap"
             self.ccp.options["fetchMarkets"] = fetch_markets_config
+            if use_testnet:
+                self.ccp.set_sandbox_mode(True)
             self._apply_endpoint_override(self.ccp)
         elif self.endpoint_override:
             logging.info("Skipping Hyperliquid websocket session due to custom endpoint override.")
         self.cca = getattr(ccxt_async, self.exchange)(creds)
         self.cca.options.update(self._build_ccxt_options())
         self.cca.options["defaultType"] = "swap"
         self.cca.options["fetchMarkets"] = fetch_markets_config
+        if use_testnet:
+            self.cca.set_sandbox_mode(True)
+            logging.info("Hyperliquid testnet mode enabled for user %s", self.user)
         self._apply_endpoint_override(self.cca)

Finding: Passivbot's complete lack of testnet support is its #1 security concern
per evaluation.md. This patch is ~8 lines, upstream-trivial. The fact that it
hasn't been added upstream despite HL's testnet being well-documented and
supported by CCXT for over a year is a signal about the bot's HL-integration
priorities — multi-exchange breadth is clearly prioritized over HL-native
safety. Users running Passivbot on HL today have no way to sandbox-test a
strategy; they go straight to mainnet.
